Cypress Functional Login Test
This repository contains functional tests for the login functionality of a web application using Cypress. The tests cover various scenarios, including valid and invalid login attempts, checking for user lockouts, and verifying the responsiveness of the application's layout across different devices and screen sizes.

Getting Started
Prerequisites
Node.js and npm should be installed on your machine.
Installation
Clone this repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone <repository-url>
cd <repository-folder>
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Running the Tests
bash
Copy code
npm run cy:open
This command will open the Cypress Test Runner, allowing you to select and run individual test cases or run all tests.

Test Scenarios
1. Login Scenarios
Login without username and password
Login with username but without password
Login without username but with password
Valid login with correct username and password
Login attempt with a locked-out user
Login attempt with a user experiencing issues
Login attempt with a user facing performance glitches
2. Session Management
Verify that the session remains active after login and navigation
3. Browser Compatibility
Ensure functionality across different browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
4. Responsive Layout
Test layout responsiveness across various devices and screen sizes:
Smartphones (e.g., iPhone SE, iPhone 8, Samsung Galaxy S5)
Netbooks (e.g., HP Mini 210, Dell Inspiron Mini)
Notebooks (e.g., Dell XPS 13, MacBook Air 13-inch)
Monitors (e.g., Full HD, 4K Ultra HD)
Reusable Functions
1. Login and Logout Functions
Reusable functions for logging in and logging out
2. Load Time Measurement
Function to measure the page load time after each test
